			"start": 7,
			"end": 1141,
			"styles": "\n\t/* Test dimension edge cases: zero, negative, decimals, signs */\n\tdiv {\n\t\t/* Zero with and without units */\n\t\tmargin: 0;\n\t\tpadding: 0px;\n\t\tborder-width: 0em;\n\t\toutline-width: 0%;\n\t\t/* Negative zero preserved like Prettier */\n\t\tright: -0px;\n\t\tleft: -0rem;\n\t\t/* Positive zero preserved like Prettier */\n\t\tfloat: +0em;\n\t\tclear: +0%;\n\t\t/* Positive sign preserved like Prettier */\n\t\tz-index: +5;\n\t\tmargin-left: +1.5px;\n\t\tmax-width: +100em;\n\t\tmin-height: +0.5rem;\n\t\t/* Negative values (lengths and percentages) */\n\t\ttop: -10px;\n\t\tleft: -2.5em;\n\t\tbottom: -1rem;\n\t\tmargin-top: -100%;\n\t\t/* Decimal values */\n\t\tline-height: 1.5;\n\t\tfont-size: 0.875rem;\n\t\twidth: 2.5vw;\n\t\t/* Leading decimal point (prettier adds leading zero) */\n\t\topacity: 0.5;\n\t\tpadding-top: 0.25em;\n\t\tpadding-left: 0.75rem;\n\t\t/* Trailing zeros */\n\t\theight: 1.5em;\n\t\tmargin-bottom: 2px;\n\t\t/* Very small values */\n\t\tletter-spacing: 0.01em;\n\t\tborder-width: 0.001px;\n\t\t/* Very large values */\n\t\tmax-width: 9999px;\n\t\tmin-height: 1000000px;\n\t\t/* Large percentages */\n\t\ttransform: scale(1000%);\n\t\t/* Mixed in shorthand */\n\t\tpadding: 0 10px 0.5em 1px;\n\t\tmargin: 1px 0 2.5rem 0px;\n\t}\n",
			"comment": null
		}
